# Orion — A Multiverse of Stories

Build a premium Electron desktop streaming app with full feature parity (and beyond) compared to Streambert, but with a completely original Netflix-inspired dark UI.

## Live Progress Tracker

Implementation progress is tracked in [`docs/orion_completion_tracker.md`](orion_completion_tracker.md). Keep that file updated as work lands so the plan remains useful during development.

Version-based implementation planning is tracked in [`docs/version_implementations.md`](version_implementations.md). That document defines Orion's own roadmap, using Streambert as the functional reference while preserving Orion's separate UI identity.

## Decisions Made

| Decision | Choice |
|---|---|
| Platform | **Electron** (request interception, ad-blocking, AllManga proxy) |
| Frontend | **React 18** + **Vite** (same stack, proven for this use case) |
| Styling | **Vanilla CSS** with CSS custom properties (design tokens) |
| Metadata | **TMDB API** (free key, prompted on first launch) |
| Anime metadata | **AniList GraphQL** (no key) |
| Streaming sources | Videasy, VidSrc, Vidking, AllManga (same as Streambert) |
| UI aesthetic | **Netflix-style dark** — clean and premium, not cosmic |
| Scope | Full feature parity + new features |
| Download tool | **yt-dlp + ffmpeg** (widely available, no custom binary needed) |
| Branding | Netflix-inspired, clean premium — no cosmic/space theme |
| Accent color | **#E50914** (Netflix red) |

