## UI/UX Design — How Orion Differs from Streambert

### Design Philosophy

Streambert has a functional but utilitarian UI — Orion should feel like a **premium streaming platform**. Key differentiators:

| Aspect | Streambert | Orion |
|---|---|---|
| Layout | Sidebar nav + content area | **Full-width immersive layout** with collapsible slim sidebar |
| Home page | Simple trending grid | **Netflix-style hero banner** with auto-rotating spotlight + categorized carousels |
| Player page | Info above, player below | **Cinema mode** — player dominates, info slides in from below |
| Navigation | Simple page state | **Smooth page transitions** with crossfade/slide animations |
| Cards | Basic poster cards | **Rich hover cards** with backdrop preview, rating, quick-play button |
| Typography | DM Sans | **Inter** (body) + **Bebas Neue** or **Outfit** (headings) |
| Colors | Flat dark (#0a0a0a) | **Layered dark** with subtle gradients, glassmorphic surfaces |
| Micro-animations | Minimal | **Everywhere** — hover lifts, skeleton loaders, progress pulses |

