## New Features Beyond Streambert

### 1. Continue Watching Row
A "Continue Watching" carousel on the home page showing items with in-progress watch progress. Streambert tracks progress but doesn't surface it prominently on the home page.

### 2. Genre Discovery Page
Browse content by genre — Streambert only has trending + search.

### 3. Hover Preview Cards
Netflix-style expanded cards on hover showing backdrop, rating, year, genres, and a "Quick Play" button — no need to navigate to the detail page for basic info.

### 4. Keyboard Navigation
Full keyboard navigation — arrow keys to browse carousels, Enter to select, Escape to go back. Streambert only has basic shortcuts.

### 5. Improved Episode Grid
TV episode grid with thumbnails (TMDB provides still images), air dates, and individual progress bars. Streambert has a simpler list.

### 6. Watch Party Indicators
Visual "New Episode" badges on TV shows in the library when new episodes air (Streambert has notifications but no visual badge in the library grid).

### 7. Smarter Source Switching
Auto-detect when a source fails (timeout/error) and offer to switch — with a "remember this choice" option per title.

